ARGUMENT 11.

1. ingenuam. Philocomasium was not ingenua, as is plain from all the references in the play. The writer of the Argu- ment was misled by 490, where not Philocomasium, but the pretended twin-sister of Philocomasium, is described as in- genua et libera. Hence patre et matre Atticis, the reading of Lorenz in v. 100, can by no means be accepted.
